      USC coach Clay Helton has friends and family affected by Hurricane Harvey and urged everyone to "do their part helping a fellow American in any way they see fit." Helton graduated from the University of Houston in 1994 and his father, Kim, served as the head coach there for seven seasons.

      UCLA coach Jim Mora and Texas A&M OC Noel Mazzone might be close friends, but there will be no "good lucks" from the two, as they prepare for Saturday's chess match against each other. "As good of friends as we are, I want to kick his tail and he wants to kick mine." Mora also said he thinks that Mazzone and his UCLA offenses got "a bad rap."

I talked to both of them this morning and they are good, their families are fine and they're focused and they're comfortable with things.       West Virginia quarterback Will Grier is so amped up to play in his first game since 2015, coach Dana Holgorsen himself is going to have to be a calming influence. "His eagerness is extremely high," Holgorsen said in a phone interview Tuesday. "He's ready to go. I've got to taper things off for him just a little bit, say, 'Look, just let it come to you. Don't be so dang geared up and fired up and excited about playing to the point where you're a little bit too juiced.' I feel like my job more than anything is to keep him calm and relaxed, and let the game come to him. He's not going to be able to make up for a year and a half in one game. But as a coach, you like to have your starting quarterback be that eager to play the game."

      Andrea Adelson ESPN Staff Writer 

      Syracuse football players will wear a memorial patch on their jerseys to honor legendary coach Dick MacPherson this season. MacPherson, a College Football Hall of Famer who made an indelible mark on the program and university, passed away earlier this month at age 86. In addition, the patch also will be displayed on the Carrier Dome field. "Our University and community will remember Coach Mac forever," athletics director John Wildhack said in a statement. "His legacy will live on in every person who had the opportunity to meet him or be in his presence. The patch on our uniforms and on the Carrier Dome field is a tribute to the lasting impact he had on Syracuse University."

      One more point on Louisville: Trevon Young has one of the best comeback stories in college football. Young is slated to start at defensive end, remarkable considering many thought his career was over after a devastating hip injury in the bowl game against Texas A&M in 2015. Young redshirted last season and worked his way back from the injury, similar to the one that ended Bo Jackson's career. After leading Louisville with 8.5 sacks in 2015, Young is a player to watch in the ACC this season without question.
